Writing command line unix programs
==================================
  1, Most important tool : getopt and friends (on most platforms)
  2, second : readline

 
Readline
--------
  http://www.delorie.com/gnu/docs/readline/rlman_toc.html
  Command completions : http://www.delorie.com/gnu/docs/readline/rlman_44.html
  rl_complete() calls rl_completion_matches() to generate list of possible
  completions. 

  For completion example, look at unix snippet fileman.c


Terminal control
----------------
  1, https://stackoverflow.com/questions/5947742/how-to-change-the-output-color-of-echo-in-linux#5947802
  2, Command : tput
  3, man 1 tput; man 5 terminfo;
  4, http://invisible-island.net/xterm/ctlseqs/ctlseqs.html#h2-PC-Style-Function-Keys
  5, https://stackoverflow.com/questions/39969495/binding-to-arrow-keys-in-readline-library?rq=1
